<h3>Publication Ethic</h3>
<p>The ANIDIP follow the ethical policies of the Editorial of the Universidad del Rosario which are applied in all its magazines.</p>
<p><strong>Copyright:</strong></p>
<p>Manuscripts submitted to each of the journals of the Universidad del Rosario must be original and unpublished and must not have been simultaneously nominated to other journals, compilations or any other means of publication. The royalties will be at the Universidad del Rosario. When the authors want to submit the manuscript to another publication, they should ask the Publisher of the Universidad del Rosario permits. Likewise, when magazines are interested in publishing articles that have been published in other journals, it shall apply for the proper permits to the owners of copyright.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities Author:</strong></p>
<p>Authors should apply his manuscripts and book reviews to ANIDIP in electronic format (Word document) to the following email address: info@iberoamericaninstituteofthehague.org in the time limits specified in the notices.</p>
<p>To consult the rules of the calls, and reviews articles authors should enter the link of calls on this page and follow the instructions: http://revistas.urosario.edu.co/index.php/anidip/pages/view / calls</p>
<p>The author must send unpublished manuscripts of unpublished book reviews. After receiving the manuscript, magazines sent them a letter of authorization for publication in which it is stated that his work is original, has not been published by any other magazine, that she respected the same way, rights intellectual property of others and he has the proper permission for the use of graphs, charts, photographs, diagrams, etc. Authors must sign and send back the magazines. Quality, rigorous research and ideas expressed in the article are the sole responsibility of these.</p>
<p>The authors accept that the manuscript be evaluated by academics, national or international peers on condition of anonymity, that is: do not know who the evaluators of the manuscript and vice versa. At the same time, the authors agree to submit the changes suggested by the evaluators within the time set by the magazines. When authors do not take into account the suggestions of the evaluators should send a letter explaining the main reasons for his choice. In any case, the magazines will take final decisions on the publication of the manuscripts once the evaluation process has ended. The magazines inform the authors if the article has been approved, approved with modifications or rejected. They can also ask the authors to review their manuscripts and send a new version. In this case, the article is put to a peer review. After receiving the final version of the document, the magazines will take the final decision on publication, at which time the authors will be informed about the approval of the document and its estimated date of publication.</p>
<p>Magazines assessors will contact any manuscript at the discretion of the editorial team, this meets the basic conditions and criteria required for the evaluation. If the manuscript does not meet these requirements, magazines authors inform the reasons why it did not proceed with the evaluation. After this first review-and if the texts exigidas- meet the conditions, the editorial team will define the manuscripts will be submitted to arbitration. At this time it will contact the right people to do the assessment. The result will be sent as soon as possible perpetrators. If the process takes longer than usual, the editor will contact these to make them aware of the situation.</p>
<p><strong>About the Reviewers:</strong></p>
<p>The evaluators selected by the Magazines can be internal or external to the Universidad del Rosario, and national or international. In any case, every manuscript that has gone through the initial filter of the editorial staff will always be evaluated by at least one external academic couple. They are people who have no conflict of interest against the authors and their works. If there is any doubt about it, another assessor will look.</p>
<p>Evaluators may suggest changes in the manuscripts in relation to background elements (theoretical, methodological and thematic) and form (spelling and typography). To cast your concept they will be guided by the assessment format of the magazine. This format contains a series of carefully selected criteria. Evaluators may approve, approve with corrections or approve manuscripts for publication.</p>
<p>1. The editors of each journal does call for the submission of articles, from which those who wish to participate they will have a specific deadline for submitting its proposal.</p>
<p>2. Upon receipt of an article, the editors of each of the magazines notify the author of receipt; will record the item and will announce the title of the work without the author\'s name, and proceeded to deliver an external evaluator pair for evaluation. The evaluators are chosen carefully taking as reference the subject of the article and expertise of each of the topics.</p>
<p>3. The external evaluators review the articles and delivered in writing the result of its assessment, filling out the evaluation form that each one of the magazines. The process of evaluation by external peers will take a period of between 4 and 5 weeks. Had tie in the decision is settled with a third evaluator.</p>
<p>4. Subsequently, acceptance, rejection, or return for adjustments or modifications will be defined.</p>
<p>5. Where appropriate, the publisher proceeds to:</p>
<p>- Communicate the author of the article and acceptance start processing the text for publication.</p>
<p>- In case of refusal to notify the author reasons given by the anonymous reviewer even preventing the publication of their work and the return of the delivered material is performed.</p>
<p>- When the pair evaluator considers that an article can be published, but it is necessary to adjust or supplement, the editors of magazines each author has written to the corresponding annotations.</p>
<p>- In any of the above three cases, the author will know the answer to anonymous evaluation, which shall be notified in writing.</p>
<p>For more detailed and specific about the process of evaluation of items go to the section ANIDIP information: peer review process on this page.</p>
<p>Editorial responsibilities:</p>
<p>The editorial team of each journal is responsible for editorial policies, publication standards and the implementation thereof in each issue. This deals with publishing, if necessary, errata, clarifications and corrections in the digital version of the magazine.</p>
<p>The editorial team is responsible for the process of manuscripts who apply to each of the magazines, and to maintain confidentiality during the process of peer review to publication of articles or when documents are removed or rejected.</p>
<p>When a number comes published, the publisher of each of the magazines is responsible for the dissemination and distribution of the number between people and institutions that have made a commitment to exchange and authors and reviewers of the articles.</p>
