<div id="history">
<h3>Journal History</h3>
<p>The Ibero-American Yearbook of International Criminal Law (ANIDIP) was founded in 2013 with the essay contest Blattmann, Odio Benito and Steiner on international criminal justice, organized by the American Institute in The Hague, with the institutional support of the International Criminal Court, the Ibero-American General Secretariat, the Coalition for the International Criminal Court (CICC), the University of El Rosario (Colombia) and the Editorial Tirant lo Blanch.</p>
<p>The international panel of essay contest, which is the ultimate selection of trials be published in the ANIDIP, has been made since its inception by a judge of the International Criminal Court (René Blattmann in 2013, Elizabeth Odio Benito in 2014 and Silvia Steiner in 2015), the Ibero-American Secretary General and President of the American Institute in The Hague.</p>
